<p>Been struggling at this for 2 hours now.</p>  <p>Basically, I'm trying to get the emails addresses from column L to be used by this script so it can send out emails to them.</p>  <p>Main error I get is: Failed to send email: no recipient (line 20, file "Code")</p>  <p>Anyone know what I can do to fix this?</p>  <p>Link to the spreadsheet can be found here:</p>  <p><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1PvLjPOtT4FZ0rqnSUHE7OxXWXNitOdS2oPFCM8iF4EE/edit#gid=1184263985" rel="nofollow">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1PvLjPOtT4FZ0rqnSUHE7OxXWXNitOdS2oPFCM8iF4EE/edit#gid=1184263985</a></p>  <pre><code>// This constant is written in column C for rows for which an email // has been sent successfully. var EMAIL_SENT = "EMAIL_SENT";  function sendEmails2() {   var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSheet();   var startRow = 2;  // First row of data to process   var numRows = 2;   // Number of rows to process   // Fetch the range of cells A2:B3   var dataRange = sheet.getRange(startRow, 1, numRows, 20)   // Fetch values for each row in the Range.   var data = dataRange.getValues();   for (var i = 0; i &lt; data.length; ++i) {     var row = data[i];     var emailAddress = row[12];  // First column     var message = row[19];       // Second column     var emailSent = row[20];     // Third column     if (emailSent != EMAIL_SENT) {  // Prevents sending duplicates       var subject = "Regarding your HackTrain application";       MailApp.sendEmail(emailAddress, subject, message);       sheet.getRange(startRow + i, 3).setValue(EMAIL_SENT);       // Make sure the cell is updated right away in case the script is interrupted       SpreadsheetApp.flush();     }   } } </code></pre>